gujarati.context:
This is the adi (opening) of a bhajan song:

He, the Harjian, who lives in Dera, is here;
The twice-born devotee, Narsi, worships Hari with folded hands.

Here is the translation:

Rich ones are devoted servants of God, it is said; 
Divine devotees, best among men, are rich in devotion to Maheshwar and Jagdishwar.

Here is the translation:

Narayana ne Narsidas, lalu beje taj jag kash;
Ramadas ne Surjaram, Rupchand chhe bhakt akam.
